## ecology & environmentalism: clicker question

Scientists should:

(a) only report results and leave others to make management decisions
(b) report results and then interpret for others involved in management decisions
(c) work closely with managers and others to integrate scientific results into management decisions
(d) actively advocate for specific natural resource management decisions
(e) make decisions about natural resource management

>

## Thinking about ecology & environmentalism

<#b2cols>

* tree huggers vs. Hummer drivers
* ecology $\\neq$ environmentalism $\\neq$ environmental science 
* ecologists (in their professional capacity) should say *what will happen*, not *what you should do* ...

